
                                            Police have confiscated stolen goods worth more than a million rand from a truck in Mpumalanga.
                                         JOHANNESBURG - Police have confiscated stolen goods worth more than a million rand from a truck in Mpumalanga. The truck was travelling from Mozambique to Gauteng on Saturday when officials stopped and searched the vehicle. The police's Leonard Hlati said: “Suspects were arrested and are expected to appear in court on Monday, 16 October.”